Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.94,0:00:05.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ten years ago while visiting the beach \Nwith my family, I met another family.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.78,0:00:12.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,While there, I got caught \Nup in a car accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.98,0:00:15.83,DCMain,DETECTIVE,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, is it true
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.83,0:00:19.76,DCMain,DETECTIVE,0000,0000,0000,,that there was another person in the car?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.76,0:00:22.33,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's what he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.15,0:00:25.62,DCMain,DETECTIVE,0000,0000,0000,,What proof do you have?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.09,0:00:29.95,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I simply thought there was another \Nsince the passenger window
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.95,0:00:31.87,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,was open all the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.62,0:00:34.71,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,The driver's seat was on the right side.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.71,0:00:36.45,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,If only one person were in the car,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.45,0:00:39.64,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,it would be strange for only the \Npassenger window to be open.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.44,0:00:46.44,DCMain,DETECTIVE,0000,0000,0000,,So, they abandoned their \Nfriend and fled alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.44,0:00:47.35,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.35,0:00:51.03,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,This man wasn't wearing his seat \Nbelt at the time of the accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.03,0:00:51.92,DCMain,DETECTIVE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.48,0:00:57.16,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm saying he struck his \Nhead on the windshield
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.53,0:01:00.26,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,when the car crashed into the guardrail.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.26,0:01:02.65,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,It broke his cervical vertebrae, \Nkilling him instantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.50,0:01:08.18,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably safe to assume the \Npassenger determined he was dead
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.18,0:01:10.26,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,when they received no response \Nafter calling out to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.26,0:01:14.64,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,so they decided to escape on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.64,0:01:18.82,DCMain,DETECTIVE,0000,0000,0000,,But why would they pretend \Nto be one of the crowd here?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.82,0:01:22.06,DCMain,DETECTIVE,0000,0000,0000,,If they were a victim of an accident, \Nthey wouldn't need to hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.73,0:01:24.76,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Probably because
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.76,0:01:29.31,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,there was a reason they had
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.35,0:01:31.82,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,to conceal themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.89,0:01:37.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Curtains rise as the headliner appears!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.79,0:01:39.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He beautifully dances his \Nmystery-solving steps!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.22,0:01:44.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The family on the beach and the car's \Nfall are both deeply shrouded in mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.50,0:01:46.29,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.29,0:01:48.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.04,0:01:50.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.98,0:03:36.98,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(397,1)}The Magician of the Waves \N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.72,0:03:35.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Magician of the Waves, Part Two!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.19,0:03:49.83,DCMain,DETECTIVE,0000,0000,0000,,A reason to conceal themselves?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.35,0:03:53.19,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Was there a robbery at a store
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.19,0:03:55.84,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,that sells watches in this area?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.84,0:03:56.46,DCMain,DETECTIVE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.26,0:04:02.15,DCMain,DETECTIVE,0000,0000,0000,,We did receive a report about \Nan hour ago that two thieves
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.15,0:04:05.92,DCMain,DETECTIVE,0000,0000,0000,,entered a watchmaker's shop about \Na kilometer from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.47,0:04:10.10,DCMain,DETECTIVE,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know about an incident that \Nhasn't been reported by the news yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.73,0:04:14.52,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,There was a bag in the back \Nseat of the sunken car.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.52,0:04:18.85,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,It was packed full of brand-name watches
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.85,0:04:21.13,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,with their price tags still on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.13,0:04:25.11,DCMain,DETECTIVE,0000,0000,0000,,They could have been wholesalers
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.11,0:04:26.70,DCMain,DETECTIVE,0000,0000,0000,,making a delivery.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.70,0:04:29.18,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Then they would've put them in plastic bags
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.18,0:04:31.37,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,or boxes so they wouldn't get damaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.00,0:04:34.67,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Only a thief concerned \Nwith stealing the watches
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.67,0:04:38.60,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,and escaping would so casually \Nstuff them into a bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.29,0:04:44.91,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Did anyone see the faces of the thieves?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.91,0:04:48.89,DCMain,DETECTIVE,0000,0000,0000,,No. They were both wearing ski masks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.38,0:04:51.89,DCMain,DETECTIVE,0000,0000,0000,,Based on their voices, we know one was a man,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.89,0:04:55.39,DCMain,DETECTIVE,0000,0000,0000,,but we don't know the gender of the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.68,0:04:56.56,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.56,0:04:58.24,DCMain,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mr. Pierrot!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.77,0:05:04.36,DCMain,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I brought all the customers who went \Nshopping after the car fell into the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.00,0:05:06.36,DCMain,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,You're sure, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.36,0:05:07.61,DCMain,SHUKICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.92,0:05:10.99,DCMain,SHUKICHI,0000,0000,0000,,This chubby man bought a \NT-shirt and swim trunks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.63,0:05:14.12,DCMain,SHUKICHI,0000,0000,0000,,This woman bought sandals.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.45,0:05:18.38,DCMain,SHUKICHI,0000,0000,0000,,And this lanky guy bought a Hawaiian shirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.84,0:05:21.30,DCMain,OAMI,0000,0000,0000,,What's the big deal, anyway?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.90,0:05:26.26,DCMain,DETECTIVE,0000,0000,0000,,It seems this man who was driving the car
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.80,0:05:28.80,DCMain,DETECTIVE,0000,0000,0000,,that fell into the water \Nhad someone with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.59,0:05:34.24,DCMain,DETECTIVE,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be questioning each of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.06,0:05:45.32,Shigekatsu,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Fukumizu Shigekatsu (32)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.11,0:05:43.18,DCMain,FUKUMIZU,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}My name is Fukumizu Shigekatsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.18,0:05:46.18,DCMain,FUKUMIZU,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I came here with my girlfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.18,0:05:50.70,DCMain,FUKUMIZU,0000,0000,0000,,When she suddenly brought up marriage \Nwhile we were on a rubber boat,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.29,0:05:54.95,DCMain,FUKUMIZU,0000,0000,0000,,I told her it was too soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.75,0:06:00.46,DCMain,FUKUMIZU,0000,0000,0000,,So she pushed me into the ocean, \Nand my clothes were soaked.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.04,0:06:04.15,DCMain,FUKUMIZU,0000,0000,0000,,By the time I returned to \Nthe boat, she was gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.15,0:06:07.47,DCMain,FUKUMIZU,0000,0000,0000,,Only my wallet remained.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.26,0:06:10.62,DCMain,FUKUMIZU,0000,0000,0000,,So I took off my soaking clothes
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.62,0:06:13.97,DCMain,FUKUMIZU,0000,0000,0000,,and bought a T-shirt and swim trunks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.50,0:06:17.49,DCMain,DETECTIVE,0000,0000,0000,,Where is your girlfriend now?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.49,0:06:22.20,DCMain,FUKUMIZU,0000,0000,0000,,She was pretty angry, so she probably \Ntook the car home without me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.20,0:06:23.98,DCMain,FUKUMIZU,0000,0000,0000,,It's her car.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.30,0:06:26.08,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the rubber boat?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.08,0:06:27.55,DCMain,FUKUMIZU,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.55,0:06:31.63,DCMain,FUKUMIZU,0000,0000,0000,,Bringing it home with me would \Nbe a pain, so I abandoned it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.63,0:06:33.99,DCMain,FUKUMIZU,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it drifted away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.96,0:06:44.92,Yasue,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Kitamori Yasue (27)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.48,0:06:42.18,DCMain,KITAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Kitamori Yasue is my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.18,0:06:45.54,DCMain,KITAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I came here to pick up guys,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.54,0:06:47.97,DCMain,KITAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,but couldn't find any good ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.28,0:06:51.01,DCMain,KITAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,On top of that, the straps \Non my sandals broke,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.42,0:06:54.04,DCMain,KITAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,so I bought some new ones \Nand was on my way home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.93,0:06:57.68,DCMain,KITAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I did get to swim quite a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.68,0:07:00.91,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Where are the sandals with the broken strap?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.61,0:07:03.98,DCMain,KITAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,I threw them away somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.00,0:07:06.73,DCMain,KITAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're handsome.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.91,0:07:13.30,DCMain,DETECTIVE,0000,0000,0000,,How did you get here dressed like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.30,0:07:15.37,DCMain,KITAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,I carried my wallet here and took a taxi.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.80,0:07:19.18,DCMain,KITAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,I kept my wallet in a locker while swimming,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.18,0:07:21.97,DCMain,KITAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,and anything I needed could be bought here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.97,0:07:23.93,DCMain,KITAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,The less you're carrying,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.93,0:07:27.63,DCMain,KITAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,the easier it is to go back to a guy's place.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.25,0:07:31.76,DCMain,OAMI,0000,0000,0000,,You've got it all wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.05,0:07:34.26,DCMain,OAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Someone stole my bag!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.51,0:07:40.64,Raiya,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Oami Raiya (26)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.66,0:07:37.63,DCMain,OAMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}While I was showering after my swim,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.63,0:07:40.64,DCMain,OAMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}someone took my bag!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.89,0:07:44.16,DCMain,OAMI,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I'm only wearing a speedo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.16,0:07:49.04,DCMain,OAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I had no choice but to buy a three \Nthousand yen shirt from that beach hut.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.04,0:07:51.15,DCMain,DETECTIVE,0000,0000,0000,,They didn't take your wallet?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.52,0:07:52.54,DCMain,OAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Nah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.54,0:07:55.26,DCMain,OAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I folded my wallet into my towel
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.26,0:07:58.16,DCMain,OAMI,0000,0000,0000,,while I was showering.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.44,0:08:01.80,DCMain,DETECTIVE,0000,0000,0000,,So, Oami-san, why did you come here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.80,0:08:02.64,DCMain,OAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.64,0:08:05.42,DCMain,OAMI,0000,0000,0000,,To hit on women.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.65,0:08:10.67,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Do you use those watches you have \Non both wrists to hit on women?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.67,0:08:12.51,DCMain,OAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.98,0:08:16.82,DCMain,OAMI,0000,0000,0000,,This one's on Japan time, and \Nthis one's on New York time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.36,0:08:18.68,DCMain,OAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Fashionable, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.55,0:08:30.69,DCMain,YUSAKU,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Yukiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.15,0:08:35.59,DCMain,YUSAKU,0000,0000,0000,,I told you not to call since \NI'd be writing until dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.59,0:08:38.70,DCMain,YUSAKU,0000,0000,0000,,Go enjoy yourselves at the beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.90,0:08:39.93,DCMain,YUSAKU,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.93,0:08:45.21,DCMain,YUSAKU,0000,0000,0000,,A car fell at the beach, \Nand the driver's dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.50,0:08:49.66,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently he was a thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.66,0:08:54.82,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,His accomplice escaped from the sunken car,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.82,0:08:58.22,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,and they've blended in with \Nthe crowd on the beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.58,0:09:02.01,DCItalic,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,If I send you photos of the three \Nsuspects, can you tell me who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.01,0:09:04.03,DCItalic,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.33,0:09:09.60,DCItalic,YUSAKU,0000,0000,0000,,She may be curious, but I can't \Nfigure it out based on photos alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.92,0:09:16.24,DCItalic,YUSAKU,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.36,0:09:20.24,DCMain,MASUMI,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I said!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.24,0:09:25.75,Parking,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Atsuhama Beach Parking Lot
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.42,0:09:25.75,DCMain,MASUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let anyone wet or \Nwearing a swimsuit leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.95,0:09:29.00,DCMain,MASUMI,0000,0000,0000,,More people are leaving!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.22,0:09:31.39,DCMain,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,Masumi, that's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.08,0:09:33.35,DCMain,MASUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.94,0:09:41.02,DCMain,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,You know we can't get involved in a case.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.02,0:09:42.64,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.04,0:09:45.66,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Case closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.33,0:09:49.47,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,All we have to do now is name the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.19,0:09:50.86,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.66,0:09:54.97,DCItalic,MASUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Case...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.50,0:09:57.02,DCItalic,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,...closed?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.66,0:10:03.49,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What? No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.07,0:10:05.75,DCItalic,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,You know who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.75,0:10:09.26,DCItalic,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,But I only sent you photos \Nof the three suspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.26,0:10:13.50,DCMain,YUSAKU,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that why you called me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.50,0:10:16.46,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd tell you more
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.46,0:10:20.39,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,about the case after I sent the photos.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.62,0:10:24.12,DCItalic,YUSAKU,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you go ahead and tell me, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.12,0:10:25.51,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.51,0:10:28.92,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I already told you that when \Nthe car fell into the ocean,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.92,0:10:31.82,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,the driver died.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.82,0:10:37.25,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,But the passenger escaped from the car,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.25,0:10:41.37,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,and blended in with the crowd, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.57,0:10:45.84,DCMain,YUSAKU,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, and that he's a thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.84,0:10:49.35,DCMain,YUSAKU,0000,0000,0000,,The story was just posted online.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.62,0:10:56.38,Watchmaker,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Watchmaker Attacked! Robbers On The Run
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.05,0:10:53.91,DCMain,YUSAKU,0000,0000,0000,,A nearby watchmaker was \Nattacked by a pair of thieves,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.91,0:10:56.38,DCMain,YUSAKU,0000,0000,0000,,and they're still on the run.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.58,0:10:57.53,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.53,0:11:00.72,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,We think one of them bought something
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.72,0:11:03.88,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,to pass themselves off as one of the crowd.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.88,0:11:05.87,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,The three people who went shopping
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.87,0:11:09.89,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,at the beach hut after the \Ncar fell are our suspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.37,0:11:11.79,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,The chubby man got soaked
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.79,0:11:14.92,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,when his girlfriend pushed him \Noff a boat and into the ocean,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.92,0:11:17.30,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,so he bought a T-shirt and swim trunks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.30,0:11:19.99,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,The young woman who came to pick up men
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.99,0:11:24.40,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,bought new sandals since \Nthe strap on hers broke.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.40,0:11:29.72,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,The flashy guy who came to hit \Non women had his clothes stolen,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.72,0:11:32.37,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,so he bought a three thousand \Nyen Hawaiian shirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.60,0:11:35.13,DCMain,YUSAKU,0000,0000,0000,,I see. I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.28,0:11:37.27,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Knew what?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.27,0:11:41.43,DCItalic,YUSAKU,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit is most likely the \Nwoman who bought the sandals...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.80,0:11:41.43,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The woman who bought the sandals...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.99,0:11:43.84,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Kitamori Yasue-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.82,0:11:48.43,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,You were riding in the car \Nthat fell, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.43,0:11:50.02,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What? No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.02,0:11:52.56,DCItalic,YUSAKU,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Is it really that surprising?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.56,0:11:53.86,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.86,0:11:58.19,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,A young man on the beach \Njust said the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.19,0:12:00.15,DCMain,KITAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.15,0:12:02.82,DCMain,KITAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,How does buying sandals make me the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.05,0:12:05.36,DCMain,KITAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,Look at how I'm dressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.36,0:12:08.46,DCMain,KITAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,I obviously came here to swim.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.46,0:12:09.70,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.46,0:12:15.17,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,If what you're wearing is \Nactually a swimsuit, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.84,0:12:23.48,DCMain,DETECTIVE,0000,0000,0000,,Are the clothes she's wearing not a swimsuit?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.48,0:12:25.05,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Probably not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.65,0:12:30.81,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,When she escaped from the sinking car, \Nshe was wearing pants or a skirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.24,0:12:35.06,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,She found herself on a public \Nbeach when she surfaced.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.38,0:12:37.20,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,If she exited the water \Nin what she was wearing,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.20,0:12:39.94,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,she'd be exposed as the passenger in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.40,0:12:44.79,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,So in the water, she took off the pants or skirt
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.79,0:12:48.84,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,she was wearing. and wrapped her \Nscarf around her waist like a wraparound.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.84,0:12:53.28,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Then she tied up the hem of her shirt \Nso she could pretend to be a swimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.95,0:12:58.84,DCMain,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,But the other two guys \Ncould've done the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.72,0:13:02.90,DCMain,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,And the woman only bought sandals.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.90,0:13:07.95,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, it's more accurate to \Nsay she could only buy sandals.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.95,0:13:09.01,DCMain,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.31,0:13:11.02,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,When she fell into the ocean,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.02,0:13:14.70,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,her wallet was submerged, \Nand her bills got wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.70,0:13:17.42,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,She could only use her change.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.97,0:13:22.02,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,So I thought the woman who \Ntook off her wet shoes
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.02,0:13:25.55,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,and bought the sandals she could afford
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.92,0:13:27.91,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,with a single coin must be the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.07,0:13:33.38,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,As you can see, unless you're \Nright on the water's edge,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.38,0:13:36.91,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,the sand's too hot to walk on barefoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.54,0:13:41.24,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,She could've used her wet bills,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.24,0:13:45.06,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,but the beach hut employees would've \Nremembered someone like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.45,0:13:48.97,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,And I doubt the beach hut \Naccepts credit cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.44,0:13:52.25,DCMain,DETECTIVE,0000,0000,0000,,But she could've been wearing sandals
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.25,0:13:55.85,DCMain,DETECTIVE,0000,0000,0000,,that are okay to get wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.18,0:13:57.66,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Did you forget?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.66,0:14:00.80,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,There were thieves in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.91,0:14:06.68,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,On top of that, the robbery \Noccurred just before the car fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.68,0:14:08.86,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,If they were on the run,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.48,0:14:13.87,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,it's hard to imagine she changed into \Nsandals that would be difficult to run in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.66,0:14:19.66,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Kitamori-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.12,0:14:22.03,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure that's a fake name, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.28,0:14:25.38,DCMain,YUSAKU,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.38,0:14:27.81,DCMain,YUSAKU,0000,0000,0000,,So the young man on the beach
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.81,0:14:32.01,DCMain,YUSAKU,0000,0000,0000,,is explaining exactly the \Nsame reasoning I told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.22,0:14:34.26,DCMain,YUSAKU,0000,0000,0000,,How very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.26,0:14:35.62,DCItalic,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.62,0:14:37.52,DCItalic,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Just like Sherlock Holmes would.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.07,0:14:40.19,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I can't see too well since \Nhe's wearing sunglasses,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.19,0:14:42.63,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,but he seems pretty handsome, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.63,0:14:43.90,DCItalic,YUSAKU,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.90,0:14:47.59,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, anyway, how did you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.59,0:14:48.60,DCItalic,YUSAKU,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.60,0:14:52.21,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,You said you knew who did it
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.21,0:14:54.91,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,after only looking at the photos I sent you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.17,0:14:57.75,DCMain,YUSAKU,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it was their watches.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.75,0:14:59.07,DCItalic,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Their watches?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.07,0:15:01.92,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, they \Nwere all wearing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.24,0:15:05.96,DCMain,YUSAKU,0000,0000,0000,,The chubby man's watch was displaying 1:45.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.36,0:15:10.80,DCMain,YUSAKU,0000,0000,0000,,The young man's watches both showed 2:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.09,0:15:15.12,DCMain,YUSAKU,0000,0000,0000,,But the woman's watch was displaying 10:10.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.12,0:15:18.93,DCMain,YUSAKU,0000,0000,0000,,That's one of the watches from \Nthe store that was robbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.93,0:15:23.23,DCMain,YUKIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What? Isn't the woman's watch just broken?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.23,0:15:27.44,DCMain,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I knew you're the thief, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.95,0:15:30.56,DCMain,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,You're wearing a watch \Nyou stole from the store.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.54,0:15:33.45,DCMain,KITAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about, you brat?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.74,0:15:36.86,DCMain,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Your watch is exactly \Nlike it was in the store.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.70,0:15:39.00,DCMain,KITAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,Of course it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.00,0:15:40.46,DCMain,KITAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,I bought it from a store!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.74,0:15:43.50,DCMain,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,But it's stopped at 10:10, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.18,0:15:50.26,DCMain,KITAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it probably broke \Nwhen I went in the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.26,0:15:52.38,DCMain,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,What? You mean you don't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.70,0:15:58.18,DCMain,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Watches sold in stores are \Ngenerally stopped around 10:10,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.56,0:16:01.69,DCMain,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,so you can clearly see the name of the maker.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.69,0:16:06.97,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is that true, Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.97,0:16:08.03,DCMain,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.03,0:16:11.15,DCMain,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I asked my dad about it at the \Nwatch area in a department store.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.15,0:16:12.20,DCMain,MASUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.20,0:16:15.76,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Brand-name watches have serial numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.76,0:16:17.12,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,If we look it up,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.12,0:16:20.98,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,we'll know if that watch was stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.95,0:16:24.21,DCMain,KITAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.59,0:16:27.44,DCMain,KITAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,That's how he knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.70,0:16:30.28,DCItalic,KITAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,That went well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.28,0:16:32.47,DCItalic,THIEF,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, piece of cake.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.70,0:16:35.75,DCItalic,KITA,0000,0000,0000,,Once we sell the watches, should \Nwe head to a tropical island?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.46,0:16:39.64,DCItalic,THIEF,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, don't steal the goods.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.64,0:16:42.48,DCItalic,THIEF,0000,0000,0000,,Put that watch back in the bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.48,0:16:43.02,DCItalic,KITAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.50,0:16:45.13,DCItalic,KITAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.13,0:16:47.06,DCItalic,KITAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,I bought this the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.70,0:16:49.08,DCItalic,KITAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.08,0:16:50.72,DCItalic,THIEF,0000,0000,0000,,Stolen goods can be tracked.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.72,0:16:52.19,DCItalic,THIEF,0000,0000,0000,,Put it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.19,0:16:54.39,DCItalic,THIEF,0000,0000,0000,,Put it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.39,0:16:55.61,DCItalic,KITAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,L-Look in front of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.27,0:17:08.51,DCMain,KITAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,We broke through the guardrail \Nand fell into the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.08,0:17:14.94,DCMain,KITAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,This must be what it \Nmeans to hit rock bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.10,0:17:20.22,Yasaku,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Yusaku \NIn Call
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.10,0:17:20.22,EndCall,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,End Call
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.62,0:17:23.64,DCMain,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,Shuichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.75,0:17:27.49,DCMain,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you finished?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.00,0:17:28.90,DCMain,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.19,0:17:30.17,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.03,0:17:48.69,DCMain,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,So, have you changed your mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.69,0:17:51.40,DCMain,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,You said something about \Njoining the FBI earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.40,0:17:52.53,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.53,0:17:54.92,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,My desire has only grown stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.27,0:18:00.20,DCMain,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me finding the thief \Nwho blended in with the crowd
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.20,0:18:02.34,DCMain,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,has gotten to your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.33,0:18:06.18,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I'd be lying if I said it hasn't,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.52,0:18:09.72,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,but I've tasted the thrill \Nof solving a mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.38,0:18:15.19,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,If things go well, I might even find \Nthe people who killed my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.50,0:18:19.30,DCMain,SHUKICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid, Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.84,0:18:22.59,DCMain,SHUKICHI,0000,0000,0000,,You seem like you've been possessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.01,0:18:25.15,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not possessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.15,0:18:26.82,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afflicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.82,0:18:27.25,DCMain,SHUKICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.26,0:18:32.13,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,By a fever known as curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.80,0:18:35.01,DCItalic,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,Tsutomu-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.60,0:18:40.47,DCItalic,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,He really is his son.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.20,0:18:45.97,DCMain,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,Shuichi, I wanted you to return to Japan,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.97,0:18:50.53,DCMain,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,and be a father figure \Nto Shukichi and Masumi,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.07,0:18:52.90,DCMain,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,but I've given up on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.94,0:18:56.28,DCMain,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Shuichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.21,0:19:00.71,DCMain,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,Let that fever drive you to clear
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.16,0:19:03.99,DCMain,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,the mist obscuring the truth until you die.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.73,0:19:08.54,DCMain,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,But in exchange, if you leave any \Nhaze behind, I won't forgive you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.80,0:19:14.54,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I always intended.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.86,0:19:18.70,DCMain,SHUKICHI,0000,0000,0000,,What's gotten into you, Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.70,0:19:21.86,DCMain,SHUKICHI,0000,0000,0000,,You sound just like Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.86,0:19:25.26,DCMain,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,It means starting today, I'm your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.63,0:19:28.39,DCMain,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.71,0:19:30.64,DCMain,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,The policeman's calling you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.64,0:19:34.13,DCMain,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,He wants to ask you about the \Ncase again at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.04,0:19:39.19,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll let you handle that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.56,0:19:42.30,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who identified \Nthe truth about the watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.30,0:19:43.87,DCMain,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.29,0:19:52.25,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,After all, you're the apprentice \Nof my country's greatest detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.48,0:19:58.93,DCMain,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Your country?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.32,0:20:01.60,DCMain,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,You're English?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.60,0:20:04.51,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, although I'm an American now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.98,0:20:09.02,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, did this case help you \Nwith your detective training?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.46,0:20:11.52,DCMain,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.01,0:20:15.20,DCMain,SHUKICHI,0000,0000,0000,,You were just like Holmes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.20,0:20:16.70,DCMain,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,N-No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.70,0:20:20.28,DCMain,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Holmes is even more amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.73,0:20:23.03,DCMain,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,B-But I guess
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.56,0:20:27.03,DCMain,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,you're at least as good at Watson.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.94,0:20:33.76,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Watson, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.76,0:20:35.27,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Great.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.30,0:20:38.71,DCItalic,MASUMI,0000,0000,0000,,He smiled again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.15,0:20:43.96,DCMain,SHUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,See you later, Holmes's apprentice.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.03,0:20:49.24,DCMain,MASUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.67,0:20:52.68,DCMain,MASUMI,0000,0000,0000,,You're a magician.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.99,0:22:16.08,DCItalic,MASUMI,0000,0000,0000,,You're a magician.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.08,0:22:17.77,DCItalic,MASUMI,0000,0000,0000,,You're a magician.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.86,0:22:20.31,DCItalic,MASUMI,0000,0000,0000,,You're a magician.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.22,0:22:28.20,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're a magician.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.67,0:22:30.22,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.22,0:22:32.30,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Is there something on my face?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.30,0:22:33.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.66,0:22:36.07,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.57,0:22:41.28,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Since Sera wore a swimsuit similar \Nto the one she wore ten years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.10,0:22:46.65,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,was she trying to help me remember \Nthat we met ten years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.76,0:22:51.89,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean she knows I'm Kudo Shinichi,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.89,0:22:54.17,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,transformed into a child by a drug?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.04,0:22:59.02,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And then there's the brother \Nbetween Sera and Akai-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.80,0:23:02.52,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That must be Haneda Meijin.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.52,0:23:04.52,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They were calling him Shukichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.46,0:23:06.87,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No, more importantly,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.30,0:23:12.25,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,the face of the woman \NHaneda Meijin called Mary.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.38,0:23:16.41,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She must be the same person
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.41,0:23:19.11,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,as the Sister From Another \NDomain Sera mentioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.75,0:23:25.06,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Was she given APTX 4869
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.06,0:23:26.51,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,just like I was?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.51,0:23:29.51,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,When? Where? By whom?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.05,0:23:34.45,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like you remembered \Nme from ten years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.10,0:23:37.52,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,but you still don't know the real reason
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.72,0:23:42.74,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I call you a magician.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.94,0:24:08.96,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.20,0:23:48.84,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But why'd they send that to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.15,0:23:52.29,DCMain,TV,0000,0000,0000,,At dawn this morning, an explosion occurred
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.15,0:23:54.66,TextCrawl,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Explosion At Pachinko Parlor Sandcastle
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.15,0:23:54.66,TextCrawl - Copy,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,What Happened Inside the Closed Store?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.29,0:23:54.66,DCMain,TV,0000,0000,0000,,at pachinko parlor Sandcastle \Nlocated in Beika City, Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.94,0:24:00.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Since a hint pertaining to the bomb was \Nwritten on it, the suspect Hirukawa tore it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.64,0:24:03.84,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Which means there are still other bombs?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.46,0:24:05.44,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,We found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.15,0:24:08.96,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,It's inside a bag in a trash can!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.96,0:24:14.97,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The Pop-up Book Bomber \N(Part One)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.66,0:24:14.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is "The \NPop-up Book Bomber, Part One!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.98,0:24:34.99,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Pop-up Book
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.57,0:24:32.81,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.81,0:24:34.55,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A pop-up book!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.99,0:24:36.74,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Conan-kun, what do you and I have in common?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.99,0:24:39.99,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
